value.0: You will leave me be! I have no desire to speak with the likes of you! You disgust me!
<StartCheck>[Intimidate]</Start> I don't threaten easy. I'll just call a guard and you'll be hauled off to prison!
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> W-what? All right, all right, just don't hurt me. I'll give you what I have, and you take it and get out of my sight.
I have trusted associates that say a cure is being assembled, but something apparently disrupted the attempt. An attack, they say. And statues.
If you are looking for manpower, however, you may wish to visit the Trade of Blades mercenary enclave in the City Core.
Are you of an arcane bent? You might wish to make yourself known at the Cloaktower, right in the Beggar's Nest.
Are you a pious individual? Perhaps you would benefit from visiting the Temple of Tyr in the City Core. Also known as the Hall of Justice.
You look the type to be concerned with the interests of nature. Perhaps you should visit the Druid Tree in the Docks district.
You look a bit of a scoundrel. You may want to visit the Moonstone Mask in the City Core.
Very well, if this dreaded Wailing makes me serve as your signpost... Neverwinter is divided into a few districts, each encompassing a particular industrious theme.
Which would you have questions about? The Beggar's Nest, the Docks, the Blacklake district, the prison, or the City Core?
Bah! What should I know of that place? It's a haven for those either caged in the prison or recently released from it.
That jail is held to the thinnest thread of law by Captain Alaefin, the Head Gaoler. I have seen little of him since the cursed Wailing came.
Castle Never is the city's heart. The "upper square" around it contains important spiritual and cultural institutions.
<StartCheck>[Intimidate]</Start> Yeah. I could kill you easy. Be safe. Pay me to go away.
